                    <h2>Hardware Encryption</h2>
                    <p>In this project, I explored the role of hardware encryption 
                        in securing automotive systems, wireless sensor networks, 
                        instant messaging, and IoT devices. My research highlights
                        the shift from traditional Trusted Platform Modules (TPMs)
                        to firmware-based TPMs, embedded directly within CPUs.
                        This integration enhances system security and efficiency.
                        Key findings from IEEE papers emphasize how hardware encryption 
                        improves energy efficiency, operational speed, and resilience 
                        against cyber threats.</p>
                </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="project">
                <img src="/images/P2.jpg" height="220" width="220">
                <ul class="p-comments">
                    <h2>CryptoMine Network Configuration</h2>
                    <p>Through collaborative work, I helped develop a comprehensive network solution 
                        for CryptoMine, a newly merged cryptocurrency mining company with 
                        branches across North America. Using Cisco Packet Tracer, our team 
                        configured a dedicated WAN using BGP to connect offices in Chicago, 
                        Vancouver, Toronto, and Mexico. The project included setting up VLANs, 
                        EtherChannel, OSPF routing, BGP, inter-VLAN routing, and trunking 
                        across multiple sites. We also designed a secure remote access solution 
                        from Ontario Tech Residence, allowing full management of the network 
                        infrastructure.</p>
                </ul>
            </article>

